3a+b=c \implies 3(ka)+(kb)=(kc)
 a + b + 2c = 2d \implies (ka) + (kb) + 2(kc) = 2(kd)
3a_1+b_1=c_1 \text{ and }3a_2+b_2=c_2 \\ \implies 3(a_1+a_2)+(b_1+b_2)=(c_1+c_2)
a_1 + b_1 + 2c_1 = 2d_1 \text{ and }a_2 + b_2 + 2c_2 = 2d_2 \\ \implies (a_1+a_2) + (b_1+b_2) + 2(c_1+c_2) = 2(d_1+d_2)
